          Preliminary support is added for authorization with two-legged OAuth
        %br
        See the -o flag.
        %br
        %br

      %li
        %b
          The RHEV-M import timeout interval is now configurable
        %br
        You can set it via the optional new "timeout" key in /etc/iwhd/conf.js.

    %h3 Bug fixes

    %ul
      %li
        %b
          iwhd now continues to work properly when mongo dies and is
          restarted
        %br
        Prior to this release, it would dump core due to an unhandled
        SocketException.
        %br
        %br

      %li
        %b
          iwhd's /etc/init.d startup script now reports failure reliably
        %br
        For example, when failing to start because no MongoDB server is
        running.  Prior to this release, it would print [FAILED], but
        mistakenly exit with status 0 (success). Now it exits with status 1
        to properly indicate an error.
        %br
        %br

      %li
        %b
          Improved handling of RHEV-M 2.x template imports  
        %br
        Adapt to a slight variation in the status report of a template import
        action in RHEV-M 2.x.
        %br
        %br

      %li
        %b
          Time limits on RHEV-M imports have been relaxed
        %br 
        dc-rhev-image now allows a RHEV-M import to take 10 minutes.
        Previously, it would timeout after just 1 minute, which was often
        inadequate.
